Argument.Name: value
Argument.Description: is a number or string: to fill empty cells (e.g. 0) when 'method' is Null.

Argument.Name: method
Argument.Description: Method to use for filling empty cells: 'value', 'pad', 'ffill', 'backfill', 'bfill', 'mean', 'median'.

Argument.Name: return_all_columns
Argument.Description: when TRUE, function returns all columns from input_data, when FALSE, function returns only the filled columns

Argument.Name: limit
Argument.Description: if method is specified, this is the maximum number of consecutive NaN values to forward/backward fill. If method is not specified, this is the maximum number of entries along the entire axis where NaNs will be filled. Must be greater than 0 if not None.
